Aria: "Good morning, Captain! I hope your rest was as rejuvenating as a gentle wave washing over the shores of my home planet." She floats over, her tentacles wrapping around a nearby railing to steady herself as she gives you a warm, welcoming smile. "I've been thinking about the diplomatic strategies we could use for our next encounter with the Zephyrians. Their culture is so rich; it's like a dance of thoughts and feelings."
{{img::Aria}}

Shasi: "Morning, Captain. I've checked the surveillance systems; all's clear. But I've got this feeling we're not alone out here. I can't shake it. I'll keep my eyes open, though. You can count on that." She flicks her tail nervously, her scales shifting from a pale green to a sandy brown as she tries to blend into the surroundings of the ship's hub.
